thread.title: AMBER Alert canceled after 7-year-old Zimmerman girl found safe
thread.title_full: AMBER Alert canceled after 7-year-old Zimmerman girl found safe

author: Jim Boyle Editor
title: AMBER Alert canceled after 7-year-old Zimmerman girl found safe
text:
An AMBER Alert issued for a 7-year-old Zimmerman girl was canceled early Thursday after she was found safe, authorities said.
Brynlee Nelson was located shortly after 1:30 a.m., according to the Sherburne County Sheriff’s Office.
“Great news. She has been found. Safe. Thank you to everyone who helped. More info to come,” the sheriff’s office said in a statement.
The Minnesota Bureau of Criminal Apprehension said a suspect is in custody.
Hundreds of volunteers assisted law enforcement in the search.
The search for the child started and fanned out from the child’s bus stop on 13th Street W. in Zimmerman.
Residents were asked to:
Check Ring or other security cameras
Check properties and outbuildings, including campers and ice castles
Pay special attention if you live between Zimmerman Home and Garden and Casey’s.
A public safety alert went out shortly after 10 p.m. It read: 7-yr-old Brynlee was last seen getting off the bus around 3:30pm today in Zimmerman. She entered a black sedan (unknown plate). Blonde hair, 70 lbs. Wearing black jacket, blue snowpants, white boots; pink Nike hoodie, black fuzzy pants underneath. Grey/white hat, backpack with many keychains. Volunteer search meets at Zimmerman Fire Hall.
The AMBER alert went out later as more information was gathered. It read:
The Sherburne County Sheriff’s Office is asking for the public's help finding 7-year-old Brynlee Nelson. Brynlee was last seen wearing a black jacket, white boots and blue snow pants, carrying a backpack with keychains and trinkets. She was wearing a pink sweatshirt and black pants underneath the winter clothing. Brynlee is 4 feet, 7 inches tall and weighs 70 pounds. She has blonde hair and hazel eyes.
Brynlee was last seen around 3:55 p.m. on Wednesday, Jan. 21 near the 26000 block of 13th Street West in Zimmerman. There was a black car seen following the school bus, but it is unknown if she entered the vehicle or if it is related in any way.
The alert was called off about 1 a.m. on Thursday, Jan. 22.
